                1
            

                By: 


                These people are total crooks! When I finally got their online system to work and was able to down load my mortgage payment history I noticed a bunch of irregularities. The biggest was that the interest verses principal of each payment varied a lot from month to month. After 5 years of paying this loan, I had hardly paid anything on the principal. When I made extra principal payments along with my regular payment, they just applied it as if it were a normal payment and most of the extra principal payment went straight to interest. So, when I made an extra $250 principal payment along with my regular monthly payment about 3/4ths of the $250 was put toward interest. I did an amortized loan schedule and when doing a comparison of an amortized schedule with their payment history, it was clear that this loan would never be paid off until it was something like 33 years old. The original term was 25 years. I contacted them about this and just got a run around. I took the printouts to a competent lawyer and he and his accountant reviewed the information and said that Southstate's accounting was very unusual and strongly suggested I refinance, which I did. I would strongly suggest that no one do business with these people.… read more


