                By: swilsonsr


                My wife & I were customers of First Federal of Charleston for more than 30 years prior to South State Bank adsorbing them along with several other banks. First Federal of Charleston was a community oriented bank that actually had a pulse on the needs of individual clients. We were very pleased to be part of First Federal of Charleston and loyally supported them throughout those 30+ years. This was partly due to the grace that was extended to us during difficult times. By this, I am speaking about those times that my family and I felt the hand of financial hardship that has befallen many of their customers. They would work with us and help us during these times and because of this we felt the need to return their goodness during our financial prosperity. We were very pleased to be part of what we felt was a "family". They knew us not only by name, but also by our troubles and our successes. However, my family and I are very disappointed by the "corporate" bank of South State. I recently had the very distinct displeasure of speaking with an employee about different issues I've noticed since their takeover. There was no grace, no understanding, no warmth, just the cold indifference of another corporation where we are known not by name, only a number and all that matters is what I refer to as their "rules of engagement". Please don't misunderstand me, I know that a business must make a profit to be solvent, but are we as their customers not more than a number or statistic. While my family and I are not rich, nor are we poor, we do at times need grace shown as many others can attest to. This is why we are diligently searching for a bank that can fill those old shoes of First Federal of Charleston.… read more


